casedialog.caseexplain: Use cases to log infractions and punishments in your guild.
casedialog.caseexplain2: If your guild is configured, MASZ will automatically manage your punishment and notify both your guild and the user.
casedialog.templateexplain: No template that matches your requirements? Create one at the end of the dialog!

casedialog.title: Title
casedialog.titleinvalid: Title field is required and can only be 100 characters long.
casedialog.punishmentexplained: MASZ will automatically manage your punishment and remove it after the specified time. You can also change the punishment if necessary.
casedialog.punishmentexplained2: The punishment will be permanent if no time is entered.
casedialog.filesexplain: You can upload files to MASZ as proof. Please note that everyone will be able to see them!

auditlog.title: AuditLog
auditlog.explain: Use auditlogs to log certain events in your guild.
auditlog.explain2: On certain events you can filter events based on channels or roles.

automods.title: Automod configuration
automods.explain: Use automoderation to automatically delete messages in certain channels or punish members on certain events
automods.explain2: You can also define filters for each event to fine tune your automoderation.

zalgo.title: Zalgo
zalgo.explain: Use this feature to automatically rename users who use zalgo in their username or nickname.
zalgo.enable: Enable zalgo moderation in this guild
zalgo.renamenormal: Try to rename users with zalgo to normal text that still sounds like their username
zalgo.renamefallback: Fallback to this string as rename option
zalgo.allowedpercentage: Allowed percentage of zalgo characters in a username or nickname
zalgo.logtomodchannel: Log all zalgo moderations to the internal webhook

config.title: Guild config

permissions.title: Permissions
permissions.explain: Here you can define which roles should have further access in MASZ.
permissions.appealafterxdays: Allow ban appeal after x days
permissions.strictpermissionsexplained: If enabled, moderators need a discord role with ban permission to create ban modcases

mutedroles.title: Muted roles
mutedroles.explain: Here you can define which roles should be used to mute users.
mutedroles.explain2: If none are defined, MASZ will use Discord's timeout functionality instead.

notifications.title: Notifications
notifications.explain: Use these webhooks to notify users or staff on MASZ events

information.title: Information
information.publicembedmodeexplained: This mode enables detailed embeds when linking modcases in discord. This will disclose private information like the suspect, punishments etc.
information.publishmodexplained: A suspect will be able to see which moderator punished them.

misc.title: Miscellaneous
misc.whoisexplained: Automatically sends information about the joined user to your internal webhook.

config.deleteresources: Delete all data (infractions, configs, event, files)
config.deleteundone: This action is not reversible. The guild is deleted immediately.

embed.title: Embed
embed.explained: This setting will change the content of the embed when your MASZ instance is linked in Discord.
embed.explained2: Please note that this might take up to one hour to update in discord.
embed.titleinvalid: The title field is required and has to be less than 256 characters long.
embed.descriptioninvalid: The description field is required and has to be less than 4096 characters long.

infrastructure.title: Infrastructure
infrastructure.explained: MASZ will use this language as the default language whenever possible. However, possibly only an english version is available for certain texts. Guild specific settings overwrite this setting.
infrastructure.explained2: Use a private webhook accessible for siteadmins only since it may log sensitive information.
infrastructure.explained3: Enable this to allow public access to all uploaded files.

tokens.title: Tokens
tokens.tabledescription: As a siteadmin you can use the MASZ API to implement your own custom scripts and automate stuff on MASZ. Create an API key below to authorize yourself against the API while making web requests. Include tokens in the "Authorization" header with a "Bearer " prefix.
tokens.name: Name
tokens.powerful: An API key is very powerful and can control everything on MASZ!
tokens.unique: This is your unique token and it is non-recoverable. If you lose this API key, you will have to reset it.
tokens.onlyone: Currently you can only create one token.
